                                <p>
                                    Dear delegates,
                                </p>
                                <p>As the Chairperson of the United Nations Special Committee on Palestine, it is both my honour and privilege to welcome you to the 10th annual DSMUN Conference. My name is Dhruv Kharabanda and I am currently a student of the 12th Grade studying the IB Diploma. I am passionate about history, politics and football. Apart from this my interests lie in acting, quizzing, writing and of course, Model UN. I began MUNning when I was in Grade 10 and since then I have attended various conferences, both national and international. In the time that I have spent MUNning I have grown a special attachment towards crisis committees that have an agenda with significant political and diplomatic implications. It is with this idea in mind that this committee was thought of.</p>
                                <p>The Israeli-Palestine issue can be considered to be one of the most contentious and globally engaging issues of modern times. Encompassing countries ranging from Saudi Arabia to United States of America, the conflict between the two has always led to great tensions. The conflict as we know it today (the formation of Israel) has its roots in the UNSCOP meeting of 1947.</p>
                                <p>We at DSMUN, make an effort to make the committees more interesting and engaging and it is with this ideal in mind that this year the UNSCOP will be executed a bit differently. The original composition of the UNSCOP was 11 member states but in this updated version where we have taken the liberty to manipulate a few historical facts we shall have 30 member states including the Powerful 5 and the countries of the Arab world.</p>
                                <p>Lobbying remains at the crux of every MUN experience. As your chairperson, I will not only expect a high level of debate but will also judge the ability to lobby, cooperate and reach a pragmatic and practical solution on the Issue of Palestine.</p>
                                <p>In the end, I would just like to say that I am looking forward to seeing all of you at Chandbagh in August. The committees are obviously the most important part of the DSMUN Conference, but at the same time I will expect all of you to have fun and enjoy the beauty of monsoon at Chandbagh.</p>
                                <div class="signing-off">
